On October 30, 2018, China’s Network of Judicatures published “civil decisions at first instance in disputes over patent rights to inventions, such as Tam Wei, Ho Zhanghong, and Beijing Orange Technology Ltd.”, which discloses some details of cases in which an APP has been sued for patent infringement.
According to the three plaintiffs, “Moving service systems and methods based on mobile terminals” Patent rights holders and inventors, while the entire operation of the “windmill” application in the “trip-out” of the APP corresponds to the technical programme of patent protection in question and constitutes patent infringement.
