The regulation proposes that the lifting of a kite, balloon, perforated lights, aircraft and small aircraft be prohibited within 500 metres of each side of the high-iron electrical line.
It provides for supplementary regulations on prohibitions and restrictions affecting high iron security, based on such upper laws as the Railway Law of the People ' s Republic of China and the Regulations on the Safety of Railways, in accordance with the geographical climatic characteristics of Fujian Province, regulating construction and tree planting along high iron, further clarifying the subject matter and scope of high iron regulation and the duties and legal responsibilities of law enforcement.
