In addition, light objects along high iron lines, such as plastic sheds, colour steel plates, sunnets and low-altitude floats, plastic protective film, etc. resulting from the construction process, should be protected against high-speed rail security by the owners or users.
With regard to the characteristics of Fujian province, which is located in the hills and high-speed railway tunnels, regulations require the construction of ponds, reservoirs and dams, the opening of drains, the drilling of wells and other acts that may affect the safety of the tunnels within a 200-metre radius of the central line above the high iron tunnel.
At the same time, those responsible for violations of the provisions shall be corrected by an order of the public security organs; in the case of an aggravating circumstance, the unit shall also be fined between $5,000 and $10,000 and the individual shall be fined between $200 and $500; in the case of an aggravating circumstance, the unit shall also be fined between $10,000 and $30,000 and the individual shall be fined between $500 and $1,000.
