The Department of Health maintains close contact with the health sector and the World Health Organization, both in the country and in neighbouring areas, to monitor the epidemic closely.
To prevent human infection with avian influenza, the Health Department calls public attention to the following:
Avoid exposure to birds or their excreta; wash hands immediately if exposed;
Do not buy or carry unsanitary birds;
(b) To refrain from eating birds ' meat, internal organs, blood products and eggs that are not fully cooked;
Take care of personal hygiene and wash hands regularly;
In the event of heat, cough, respiratory difficulties, masks should be worn, medical treatment should be made available as soon as possible and doctors should be given details of the history of travel and animal exposure.
