On October 1st, China News Agency (CHO Xiaoqin Liu) amended the Protocol for the Movement Control of the Three Gorge Dam Water Hub (hereinafter referred to as the Movement Control Protocol), which became operational on October 1st, a three canyon lifter was formally deployed with the gate after two years of trial.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the waters of the three canyons, the Goku dam, are in good order.
On 30 September, at 2100 hours, the Yangtze Three Gorges Navigation Authority issued its first security clearance plan and carried out security checks on 160 vessels, with a total of 124 vessels eligible for clearance.
At 1400 hours on 1 October, the shipping sector arranged for the first pass plan following the implementation of the new regulations.
Following the implementation of the new regulations, the security screening plan was issued once a day at 0900 hours and again at 2100 hours, while the pass-through plan was issued at 1400 hours and 2000 hours respectively, to allow ships flexibility in scheduling the dam.
The Movement Control Protocol added the principle of “classification control” for the movement of ships across dams, and the prioritization of ships at dams was determined according to the functional position of the gates and lifters, and short-line passenger ships at gates were adjusted to the same level of priority as demonstration ships and good faith ships.
It is also two weeks after the piloting of the lifter, which is officially coordinated with the gate.
For the first time, the river and the three canyons of the canyon are also being prioritized by large-sized demonstration ships and new energy power vessels.
At the same time, the Movement Control Protocol adjusts the “routing movement management waters” from the previous 180 km near dam to 541.8 km from the Yunyang Yang River Bridge to the Ishi River Bridge, and divides the “core waters, near dam waters, controlled waters, movement waters”.
This has facilitated the choice of suitable water to be shut down and reduced the backlog of dam-bound ships.
The Movement Control Protocol also provides for good faith measures such as the cancellation of declarations of non-compliance and 24-hour delay in the passage of the dam, taking into account the characteristics of the existing ship crossing and the waiting period.
With the storage of water in the three canyons, the condition of navigation in the storage area has improved, contributing to the rapid development of the Yangtze shipping.
