In July, China imposed import duties on imports of United States soybeans in response to Trump ' s tariff on imports of Chinese goods.
The United States Department of Agriculture will issue a first estimate of the area to be planted next year, which will presumably include considerations of tariff implications.
The estimate is expected to confirm the anticipated reduction in soybean seeding by private institutions.
According to a report seen by Reuters, on 19 October, Informa Economics projected an increase of 4 to 92.7 million acres (37.5 million hectares) in maize cultivation in 2019 and a reduction of 7 to 83 million acres in soybeans cultivation.
Informa also projects a 4 per cent increase in wheat cultivation in the United States.
