If it does, it will be the Bank’s fifth raise in a little more than a year.
The analysts interviewed by Reuters had previously estimated an increase of 0.1 per cent.
Statistics Canada reported growth on Friday in 12 of the 20 industries.
This figure is noteworthy because this year’s central bank predicted earlier this month that temporary factors could delay the third quarter of GDP.
The Governor of the Central Bank of Canada, Polotz, promised on Thursday that the Central Bank would continue to raise interest rates gradually and would pay close attention to economic data.
The next time the Central Bank of Canada announces interest rates will be on October 24th.
The Central Bank of Canada has raised interest rates four times since July 2017 as a result of the strengthening of the Canadian economy and the near-lowest unemployment rate recorded.
Stephen Brown, a senior Canadian economist at the Kaiser macro level, said that the country ' s economy was expected to grow by about 2 per cent per annum in the third quarter of the year.
“This is going to be 1.5% higher than the Central Bank of Canada expected, and will therefore be another reason to expect the Central Bank of Canada to raise interest rates next month,” he says in a report.
